Stone, William C. - The Wall Street Transcript













































 





































William C. Stone
WILLIAM C. STONE is Chairman of the Board, President and Chief Executive
Officer of SS&C Technologies, Inc. (SS&C). SS&C is a worldwide
enterprise applications software company serving the institutional
investments industry. Mr. Stone founded SS&C in 1986 and SS&C went
public in 1996. Mr. Stone has grown SS&C to a company of over 400 people
with offices in Europe, Asia, and throughout North America. SS&C has
acquired 14 firms since 1995, most recently, Amicorp’s Fund Services
business, Investment Advisory Network, NeoVision, and OMR Systems. Mr.
Stone is a graduate of Marquette University. He holds or has held
National Association of Securities Dealers (NASD) securities series
licenses 6, 7, 8 and 22, was a New York Stock Exchange and Municipal
Securities Rulemaking Board Principal and an Associated Person with the
Commodity Futures Trading Commission. Mr. Stone is a member of the Board
of Advisors of the University of Connecticut’s School of Business.
